e’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hugues II de Fagnolles Rumigny was born about 1210, in Fagnolle, Namur, Belgium as the son of Seigneur Hugues I de Rumigny and N. de Fagnolles. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Marie NN."},"et":{"ABT 1210–":"umbes 1210–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1184–1249":"1184–1249","1249":"1249","ABT 1210":"umbes 1210","Abt 1265":"umbes 1265","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1184":"1184","of,Fagnolle,Namur,Belgium":"Fagnolle, Namur, Belgia"},"fi":{"ABT 1210–":"noin 1210–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1265–Male":"1265–Kuollut","1184–1249":"1184–1249","1249":"1249","ABT 1210":"noin 1210","Abt 1265":"noin 1265","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1184":"1184","of,Fagnolle,Namur,Belgium":"Fagnolle, Namur, Belgia"},"fr":{"ABT 1210–":"environ 1210–Décédé","1210–Male":"1210–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1265–Male":"1265–Décédé","1184–1249":"1184–1249","1249":"1249","ABT 1210":"environ 1210","Abt 1265":"environ 1265","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1184":"1184","of,Fagnolle,Namur,Belgium":"Fagnolle, Namur, Belgique","lifeSummary":"Hugues II de Fagnolles Rumigny est né environ 1210, à Fagnolle, Namur, Belgique, fils de Seigneur Hugues I de Rumigny et N. de Fagnolles. Il a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Marie NN."},"de":{"ABT 1210–":"um 1210–Verstorben","1210–Male":"1210–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1265–M